  "concept": "vuejs/core#11296: Refs get cleaned/garbage collected before the onLeave and onBeforeLeave transitions hooks",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:37.250120+00:00",
  "text": "Refs get cleaned/garbage collected before the onLeave and onBeforeLeave transitions hooks\n\n### Vue version\n\nv3.4.31\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://stackblitz.com/edit/github-gyqmpz-bdzdrb?file=src%2Fpages%2FAbout.vue\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nClicking on the navigation link will trigger navigating. In the console the refs for the pages will be logged\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe expected behavior is that the refs should trigger errors and have content within it\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nThe refs are empty\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: transition",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
